  <front>
    <title>Certificate Transparency: Domain Label Redaction</title>
    <seriesInfo name="Internet-Draft" value="draft-strad-trans-redaction-01"/>
    <author initials="R." surname="Stradling" fullname="Rob Stradling">
      <organization>Comodo CA</organization>
    </author>
    <author initials="E." surname="Messeri" fullname="Eran Messeri">
      <organization>Google UK Ltd.</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="17" month="January" year="2017"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>This document defines mechanisms to allow DNS domain name labels that
   are considered to be private to not appear in public Certificate
   Transparency (CT) logs, while still retaining most of the security
   benefits that accrue from using Certificate Transparency.</t>
    </abstract>
  </front>
